Subject: [liste-egc] CALL FOR PAPERS IDA 2021

CALL FOR PAPERS
IDA 2021
Symposium on Intelligent Data Analysis
https://ida2021.org/

Submission deadline November 27, 2020
https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=ida2021

April 26-28, 2021, Porto, Portugal

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aims and Scope
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Advancing Intelligent Data Analysis requires novel, potentially 
game-changing
ideas. IDA's mission is to promote ideas over performance: a solid 
motivation
can be as convincing as exhaustive empirical evaluation. Therefore IDA 
accepts
all inspiring papers for both presentation and publication. In order to 
create
an open atmosphere that encourages discussion, IDA symposia are 
intentionally
small-scale and single-track.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Important Dates
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Paper submission deadline: November 27, 2020
Notification of acceptance: January 22, 2021
Camera-ready paper submission deadline: February 22, 2021
Latest early registration: April 1, 2021

All dates are 23:59:59 SST (Standard Samoa Time / Anywhere on Earth)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Venue
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

IDA 2021 will be held in April 26-28, 2021 in Porto, Portugal.

The conference will take place in the Faculty of Medicine of University of
Porto, Portugal.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Additional Information and Submission Details
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contributions, written in English, must be formatted according to the
guidelines of the Lecture Notes of Computer Science (LNCS) series by 
Springer-
Verlag, which are available together with templates here:
https://www.springer.com/gp/computer-science/lncs/conference-proceedings-
guidelines. We strongly recommend using the LNCS template for LaTeX. The 
page
limit for any contribution, including figures, title pages, references, and
appendices, is 10-12 pages in LNCS format.

Authors may not submit any paper which is under review elsewhere or 
which has
been accepted for publication in a journal or another conference; 
neither will
they submit their papers elsewhere during the review period of IDA 2021.

